cial UK Charts Company|accessdate=15 December 2016}}</ref>\n* [[House music|house]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Smirke|first1=Richard|title=Clean Bandit Puts Classical Music In The House With 'Rather Be'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6128772/clean-bandit-puts-classical-music-in-the-house-with-rather-be|website=[[Billboard.com]]|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Carley|first1=Brennan|title=Q&A: Jess Glynne on Her \u2018Surreal\u2019 Grammy Win for Best Dance Recording|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6128772/clean-bandit-puts-classical-music-in-the-house-with-rather-be|website=[[Spin.com]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n* [[dance-pop]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Daw|first1=Robbie|title=Spring 2014 Playlist: 11 Hot Imports You Should Be Listening To, From Allie X To Katy B To Zhala|url=http://www.idolator.com/7513503/11-hot-imports-kiesza-katy-b-clean-bandit|website=[[Idolator.com]]|publisher=SpinMedia|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Caviness|first1=Tod|title=Come Out With Pride features rainbow of activities in Orlando|url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/os-come-out-with-pride-orlando-20140923-story.html|website=[[Orlando Sentinel]]|publisher=Orlando Sentinel|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Euro house]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Jenkins|first1=Craig|last2=White|first2=Caitlyn|last3=Lipshutz|first3=Jason|last4=Mapes|first4=Jillian|last5=Larson|first5=Jeremy D.|last6=Brown|first6=Harley|title=BSBB Round 1: Clean Bandit feat. Jess Glynne, \"Rather Be\" vs. Hozier, \"Take Me To Church\"|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/best-song-bracket-2014/6406161/bsbb-round-1-clean-bandit-feat-jess-glynne-rather-be-vs|website=Billboard.com|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n* [[deep house]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cridlin|first1=Jay|title=With 'Rather Be,' Clean Bandit leading a retro dance revolution|url=http://www.tampabay.com/things-to-do/music/with-rather-be-clean-bandit-leading-a-retro-dance-revolution/2222419|website=[[Tampa Bay Times]]|publisher=Tampa Bay Times|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n| length     = 3:47\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Clean Bandit|Jack Patterson]]\n* [[Jimmy Napes|James Napier]]\n* Nicole Marshall\n* [[Grace Chatto]]\n| producer   =\n* Grace Chatto\n* Jack Patterson\n| chronology = [[Clean Bandit]]\n| prev_title = [[Dust Clears]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Extraordinary (Clean Bandit song)|Extraordinary]]\n| next_year  = 2014\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Jess Glynne]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title =\n | prev_year  =\n | title      = Rather Be\n | year       = 2014\n | next_title = [[My Love (Route 94 song)|My Love]]\n | next_year  = 2014\n}}{{External music video|{{YouTube|m-M1AtrxztU|\"Rather Be\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Rather Be'''\" is a song by the English [[electronic music]] group [[Clean Bandit]]. It features vocals by [[Jess Glynne]]. The track was released on 17 January 2014 as the fourth single from the group's debut studio album, ''[[New Eyes]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a548576/clean-bandit-announce-debut-album-new-eyes.html|title=Clean Bandit announce debut album New Eyes|last=Copsey|first=Robert|date=3 February 2014|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=3 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"itunes\" /> It also appears on the deluxe version of Glynne's debut album, ''[[I Cry When I Laugh]]'' (2015). It was co-written by band members [[Clean Bandit|Jack Patterson]] and [[Grace Chatto]], along with [[Jimmy Napes]] and Nicole Marshall, and produced by Patterson and Chatto.  [[Warner Music Group]] released a number of official remixes  for download,<ref name=\"remixesuk\"/> with DJs such as [[All About She]] and [[Cash Cash]].\n\nThe song debuted at number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]] and was the third fastest-selling single of 2014, and the highest-selling January single since \"[[Spaceman (Babylon Zoo song)|Spaceman]]\" by [[Babylon Zoo]] in 1996.<ref name=\"officialcharts.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/will.i.am-and-miley-cyrus-neck-and-neck-with-clean-bandit-in-singles-race-2760|title=will.i.am and Miley Cyrus neck-and-neck with Clean Bandit in singles race|work=officialcharts.com}}</ref> The song spent four weeks at number one, [[List of million-selling singles in the United Kingdom|selling over one million copies]] since release and becoming only [[List of Platinum singles in the United Kingdom awarded since 2000#3\u00d7 Platinum|the seventh single to go 3\u00d7 Platinum]]. In the United States, the song peaked at number ten on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. The song was placed at number four on ''Billboard''{{'}}s 10 Best Songs of 2014 list.<ref name=\"billboard\"/>\n\n\"Rather Be\" has also become an international hit in part due to the song's video becoming a viral hit on [[YouTube]]. Filmed in Tokyo and featuring [[Haruka Abe]], it has over 570 million views. It won the [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording|Best Dance Recording]] category at the [[57th Annual Grammy Awards|2015 Grammy Awards]] in the United States.<ref name=\"Grammy\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2014/12/05/grammy-nominees-2015-the-full-list/2/|title=Grammy Nominees 2015: The Full List|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=13 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Background and composition==\n\"Rather Be\" was written by Clean Bandit [[keyboardist]] Jack Patterson, Nicole Marshall and [[Jimmy Napes|James Napier]] (frequent collaborator of [[Disclosure (band)|Disclosure]]),<ref name=\"credits\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2013/dec/05/clean-bandit-rather-be-feat-jess-glynne|title=Clean Bandit - Rather Be feat Jess Glynne: New music|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=5 December 2013|accessdate=22 December 2013}}</ref> and was produced by Clean Bandit [[cellist]] Grace Chatto and Patterson.<ref name=\"credits\" />\n\n\"Rather Be\" performs in the key of [[G\u266f minor]], in [[common time]] and at a light [[tempo]] of 121 [[beats per minute]]. It follows a chord progression of G\u266fm\u2013D\u266fm/F\u266f\u2013E<small>maj7</small>\u2013B<ref name=\"sheetmusic\">[http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=mn0129978&ref=google#ProductDetails Clean Bandit \"Rather Be\" Sheet Music]. musicnotes. Retrieved 7 February 2014.</ref> The track's [[instrumentation]] includes a [[violin]], [[chiptune]]-style synth blips, a slow bass, piano and vocals. According to [[Pandora.com]], the song features a \"vocal counterpoint\", a subtle \"buildup/[[breakdown (music)|breakdown]]\", use of \"modal harmonies\", the use of \"chordal patterning\" and \"[[staccato]] synths\".<ref name=\"Pandora\">{{cite web|url= http://www.pandora.com/clean-bandit/new-eyes/rather-be-feat-jess-glynne|title=Pandora - Rather Be (Feat. Jess Glynne)|accessdate=2 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Release and critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1=[[Contactmusic.com]]\n|rev1Score={{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"contactmusic\">{{cite web|last=Williams|first=Holly|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/single-review/clean-bandit-rather-be|title=Clean Bandit - Rather Be Feat. Jess Glynne Single Review|publisher=[[contactmusic.com]]|accessdate=7 February 2014}}</ref>\n|rev2=[[Digital Spy]]\n|rev2Score={{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"DigitalSpy\">{{cite web|last=Copsey|first=Robert|date=6 January 2014|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/review/a541828/clean-bandit-rather-be-review-fresh-and-infectious.html|title=Clean Bandit - 'Rather Be' review: 'Fresh and infectious'|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=7 February 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n\n\"Rather Be\" received its first play on 4 December 2013, when it featured as [[BBC Radio 1]] DJ [[Zane Lowe]]'s ''Hottest Record in the World''.<ref name=\"hottest\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01mvd44|title=Hottest Record: Clean Bandit - Rather Be|publisher=BBC|date=4 December 2013|accessdate=22 December 2013}}</ref> The song's digital release date was originally planned to be 19 January 2014, but was moved to 17 January.<ref name=\"itunes\" /> The single was issued by [[Warner Music Group|Warner Music]], and is the third to be taken from Clean Bandit's debut studio album.<ref name=\"itunes\" /> Warner Music Group also released a number of official remixes released for download,<ref name=\"remixesuk\"/> with DJs such as [[All About She]] and [[Cash Cash]].<ref name=\"credits\"/>{{better source|currently offers no support|date=July 2018}}\n\nThe song was met with critical acclaim in the music press, with both positive reviews from [[Contactmusic.com|contactmusic]]<ref name=\"contactmusic\"/> and [[Digital Spy]], who commented, \"Co-penned with [[Disclosure (band)|Disclosure]] hitmaker Jimmy Napes, 'Rather Be' blends classical-inspired violin with uplifting [[house music|house]] beats and a vocal that sounds suspiciously like [[Natasha Bedingfield]]. The result is an infectious sound that feels fresh and exciting.\".<ref name=\"DigitalSpy\"/> The song was placed at number four on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s 10 Best Songs of 2014 list.<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|title=The 10 Best Songs of 2014|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2014/6405564/10-best-songs-of-2014?facebook_20141211|date=11 December 2014|accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref> In December 2014, the song received a nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording]], which it would go on to win in early 2015.<ref name=\"Grammy\"/>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nThe song debuted at number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]] and was the third fastest-selling single of 2014 (behind [[Band Aid 30]]'s \"[[Do They Know It's Christmas?#Band Aid 30|Do They Know It's Christmas?]]\" and [[Ben Haenow]]'s \"[[Something I Need#Ben Haenow version|Something I Need]]\"), and the highest-selling January single since \"[[Spaceman (Babylon Zoo song)|Spaceman]]\" by [[Babylon Zoo]] in 1996.<ref name=\"officialcharts.com\"/> It stayed there for four weeks, the longest UK number one for three years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/clean-bandit-score-fourth-week-at-the-top-with-rather-be-2295/|title=Clean Bandit score fourth week at the top with Rather Be|work=officialcharts.com}}</ref> The song spent four weeks at number one and was the second best-selling song of 2014 in the UK, [[List of million-selling singles in the United Kingdom|selling over 1.13 million copies]] by the end of the year.<ref name=\"top 40 singles 2014\"/> On the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]], the song peaked at number ten, marking Clean Bandit's and Glynne's first US top 10. The song was a remarkable success worldwide, topping the charts in 13 different countries.\n\nUpon its release \"Rather Be\" held the record for the most streams in a single week on [[Spotify]] in the United Kingdom. The track received 1.09 million plays over seven days in February 2014, surpassing the record previously held by [[Daft Punk]]'s \"[[Get Lucky (Daft Punk song)|Get Lucky]]\", although this record has now been surpassed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a550037/clean-bandits-rather-be-breaks-daft-punks-uk-spotify-record.html |title=Clean Bandit's 'Rather Be' breaks Daft Punk's UK Spotify record - Music News |publisher=Digital Spy |date=2014-02-10 |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref>\n\nThe song debuted at number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]]. It became the fasting-selling single of 2014, selling 163,000 copies in its first week. January is usually a month of low single sales. However, \"Rather Be\" bucked that trend, recording the biggest weekly sale for a January number one since [[Babylon Zoo]]'s \"[[Spaceman (Babylon Zoo song)|Spaceman]]\", which was released in January 1996.<ref name=\"OCC\">{{cite web|last=Official Charts Company|title=Clean Bandit score huge-selling Number 1 single with Rather Be|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/clean-bandit-score-huge-selling-number-1-with-rather-be-2752/|accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref> In total, \"Rather Be\" spent four weeks at number one. In August 2015, the [[British Phonographic Industry]] certified the song 3\u00d7 Platinum (the sixth song of the century to achieve this).<ref name=\"Cert\">[http://www.bpi.co.uk/certified-awards.aspx \"British single certifications \u2013 Clean Bandit feat. Jess Glynne \u2013 Rather Be\".] British Phonographic Industry. ''Enter'' Rather Be ''in the field Search. Select'' Title ''in the field'' Search by. ''Select'' single ''in the field'' By Format. ''Click'' Go</ref> It stayed in the top 75 for 73 weeks, setting the record for the longest unbroken run (since equalled by \"[[Thinking Out Loud]]\" by [[Ed Sheeran]]).  As of September 2017, the song has sold in the UK 1,283,000 copies in pure sales, it also gained 93 million in streams, making a total of 2,219,000 in combined units.<ref name=\"uk sales\">{{cite news |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-uks-official-chart-millionaires-revealed__20459/ |title=he UK's Official Chart 'millionaires' revealed |first= Rob |last=Copsey |work=The Official Charts Company |date=19 September 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was directed by the group and was uploaded to [[YouTube]] on 5 December 2013. It has since received more than 570 million views.<ref name=\"YouTubeDec2013\">{{YouTube|id=m-M1AtrxztU|title=\"Rather Be\"}}</ref> The video was filmed in [[Tokyo]], Japan and features [[Haruka Abe]] as a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] fan. During the video, Abe lip-syncs to Jess Glynne's vocals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Clean Bandit website|url=http://cleanbandit.co.uk/news/}}</ref> The band comments:\n\n<blockquote>\"The video is about a Japanese fan of the band who becomes delirious and has hallucinations of band members and our logo appearing unexpectedly in her daily life as a chef. Filming in Tokyo was an amazing experience: we spent almost a week there and everyone was so helpful. We made it ourselves as always, which was quite scary as we've never produced anything so far away before. We had a bit of trouble filming the scene on the train though. Turns out it's considered incredibly rude to make noise on a train so when we started dancing around to the track in the carriage with the extras, it didn't go down well! Got shouted at.\"<ref>[http://wjlondon.com/track-week-clean-bandit-ft-jess-glyne-rather/ Track Of The Week: Clean Bandit ft. Jess Glynne \u2013 Rather Be] Joss ISM, December 6, 2013</ref></blockquote>\n\n==Live performances==\nOn 16 January 2014, the group performed \"Rather Be\" in [[BBC Radio 1]]'s ''[[Live Lounge]]'', together with a [[cover version]] of [[Lorde]]'s \"[[Royals (song)|Royals]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Clean Bandit in the Live Lounge|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/events/eccdgw|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=16 January 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref> They performed it as part of their sets at the [[Summertime Ball]], [[Glastonbury Festival|Glastonbury]] and [[T in the Park]].{{citation needed|date=July 2014}} They also performed at the [[2015 Brit Awards]] nomination launch party along with their new single \"[[Real Love (Clean Bandit and Jess Glynne song)|Real Love]]\".\n\n==In popular culture==\n{{More citations needed section|date=September 2017}}\n* In April 2014, [[The 1975]] covered the song while at the [[BBC Radio 1]] ''[[Live Lounge]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Eames|first1=Tom|title=The 1975 cover Clean Bandit's 'Rather Be' in the Live Lounge - watch|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a552144/the-1975-cover-clean-bandits-rather-be-in-the-live-lounge-watch.html|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=12 September 2014|date=18 February 2014}}</ref>\n* From September 2014 to December 2016, the instrumental of the song was used in [[Marks & Spencer]] food adverts, until January 2017 when the music was changed to [[Shape of You]] by [[Ed Sheeran]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ridley|first1=Louise|title=Marks And Spencer Is Bringing Back Its Food Porn Adverts|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/09/02/marks-and-spencer-food-pudding-advert-this-is-not-just-any_n_5751628.html|website=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=12 September 2014|format=2 September 2014}}</ref>\n* In September 2014, [[The Coca-Cola Company|Coca-Cola]] released a commercial in the United States featuring the chorus of the song.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tvcommercialssongs.com/coca-cola-rather-be/|title=Coca-Cola Rather Be|date=25 September 2014|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref>\n* In September 2014, [[YES Network]] featured the song in the closing credits montage of [[Derek Jeter]]'s final season of playing Major League Baseball.\n* The song was featured in the season 6 episode of ''[[Glee (TV Series)|Glee]]'' entitled \"[[The Rise and Fall of Sue Sylvester]]\". The song is performed by the members of The New Directions.\n*[[Adanna Duru]] covered the song on the 14th season of ''[[American Idol]]''.\n* The song was used in the [[Konami]] game, ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2016]]'' as third track.\n* The song is the backing music in 2016 for ads for [[Graton Resort and Casino]] in northern California.\n* [[Mazda]] has used the song in an Australian commercial for the  [[Mazda2]] vehicle.\n* [[Jessica Mauboy]] covered the song on her album ''[[The Secret Daughter Season Two: Songs from the Original 7 Series]]'' (2017).\n* A cover version by [[Marc Scibilia]] was featured in the 2018 [[Sony Pictures Animation]] film ''[[Peter Rabbit (film)|Peter Rabbit]]''.\n*The song was featured over the closing credits to the final episode of [[Sense8]], \"Amor Vincit Omnia\", with behind the scenes clips of the production of the show.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=\"itunes\">